    <TD>&nbsp;</TD></TR>

<TR><TD VALIGN=top ALIGN=right><A NAME=tcja><B>TCJA/DJO</B></A></TD>
    <TD>&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD VALIGN=top><A HREF=http://www.tcja.nl>TCJA/DJO</A> (<I>Technical Creative Youth
    Center Arnhem</I>, formerly known as Dutch Young Scientists).
    I'm an (active?) member of this organisation, which tries to develop
    the technical interest of children.  They provide courses for children
    in Photography, Electronics, Computers, and more.
    My most important contribution, however, is emptying the coffee
    machine. The machine fights back!</P>

    <P>Here I got <A HREF=career.html#tcja>in touch with computers</A>,
    back in 1978.</P></TD>
    <TD VALIGN=top ALIGN=center><IMG
        SRC=images/tcja.gif WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=85 BORDER=0></TD></TR>

<TR><TD VALIGN=top ALIGN=right><A NAME=volley><B>Volleyball</B></A></TD>
    <TD>&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD VALIGN=top><P>In the city-quarter in Arnhem, where I live, we have a lively
    organization with many activities.  I play volleyball: on a very low
    level, but with a lot of fun.  Want to join?  We are always in need for
    a few more players.</P></TD>
    <TD VALIGN=top ALIGN=center>&nbsp;</TD></TR>

<TR><TD VALIGN=top ALIGN=right><A NAME=ninja><B>NINJA</B></A></TD>
    <TD>&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD VALIGN=top><P><A HREF=http://www.cs.kun.nl/ninja/>NINJA</A> stands for
        "Nijmeegs Informatica Netwerk voor Alumni en Jaargroepen", in which
        respect it tries to be the intermediate between old, current, and
        future students of the
        <A HREF=http://www.cs.kun.nl>Informatics sub-faculty</A> of the
        <A HREF=http://www.kun.nl>University of Nijmegen</A>.  In my role as
        secretary of this organization, I collect addresses, sent postings,
        maintain the website, and whatever more is needed.</P></TD>
    <TD VALIGN=top ALIGN=center><IMG
       SRC=images/ninja.gif WIDTH=125 HEIGHT=94></TD></TR>

<TR><TD VALIGN=top ALIGN=right><A NAME=walk><B>Walking</B></A></TD>
    <TD>&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD VALIGN=top>Once a month, a group of people from all over The Netherlands
        meet to make a walk in nature somewhere.  Usually these walks
        are around 20 kilometers.  Some pictures can be found at my
        <A HREF=wandel/>wandel</A> page (Dutch only)</TD>
    <TD>&nbsp;</TD></TR>

<TR><TD VALIGN=top ALIGN=right><A NAME=more><B>Furthermore</B></A></TD>
    <TD>&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD VALIGN=top>
you can find me
